istent with 0.2\" resolution 32 GHz\nobservations obtained with the Very Large Array as a part of the VANDAM survey,\nsuggesting that grains have grown through coagulation. The morphology,\ntemperature, and densities of the compact structures are consistent with those\nof disks formed in numerical simulations of collapsing cores. Moreover, the\nproperties of B1b-N are consistent with those of a very young protostar,\npossibly a first hydrostatic core. These observations provide support for the\nearly formation of disks around low-mass protostars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Sep 2017 11:53:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-11"}
